nd storytelling style. Raised by her grandparents, who took her on their seasonal travels, Paul spent most of her childhood learning Sliammon ways, stories, and legends. Her adult life unfolded against a backdrop of colonialism and racism. As Paul worked to sustain a healthy marriage, raise a large family, cope with tremendous grief and loss, and develop a career and give back to community, she drew strength from Sliammon teachings, which live on in the pages of Written as I Remember It.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aComox IndianszBritish ColumbiazSunshine CoastvBiography. 0aComox IndianszBritish ColumbiazSunshine CoastxHistory. 0aComox IndianszBritish ColumbiazSunshine CoastxSocial life and customs. 0aComox Indians. 0aComox languagevTexts. 0aIndigenous peopleszBritish ColumbiazSunshine CoastvBiography. 0aLegendszBritish ColumbiazSunshine Coast. 0aLegends. 0aOral traditionzBritish ColumbiazSunshine Coast. 0aOral tradition. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Native American Studies.2bisacsh1 aJohnson, Harmony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRaibmon, Paige, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWatanabe, Honoré, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311127407208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014z978311127709708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311141999240uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077482712640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774827126423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774827126/original  a978-3-11-127407-2  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014